;; This file is part of Gaiag, Guile in Asd In Asd in Guile.

Gaiag is a implementation of the Dezyne server backend in Scheme.  It
uses a functional approach based on AST-transformations.  It can be
used standalone or use input from the OM-parser generator.

It uses some GNU Guile extensions, such as modules and GOOPS, the
object oriented extension to Guile.  Features include

   * DZN parser               produce an AST that stays close to DZN
   * object model in Goops    DZN AST/OM class definition, about 200 lines
   * semantics-resolver       resolve function or action, etc
   * name-resolver            name resolution
   * type checker             basic type checks -- INCOMPLETE
   * well-formedness checker  basic checks -- INCOMPLETE
   * code generators          c, c++, ...
   * CSP generator
   * DZN pretty printer
   * AST normalisations
   * table views              event, state
   * json2scm, scm2jon        external scripts for JSON integration pipes
   * simulator                TODO: also use pessimist approach over
                              multiple run-to-completion calls
   * test suite               250 module tests
   * code coverage stats

Using Goops introduces a significant performance penalty over using of
plain lists --a factor 5 to 15-- depending on the use of generics and
multiple dispatch.  A proof of concept to reduce this penalty to ca 5%
lives in Andy Wingo's wip-goops-refactor branch which still (Wed Aug 5
2015) has some problems.  (See git://git.savannah.gnu.org/guile).

A plain list backend for Goops-like client code is available and used
by default.  It supports (make <class>), (match o (($ <class> ...))
(is-a? o <class>) and transparent use of all slot accessors.  Client
code cannot use (define-class) or (define-method).

ROADMAP
=======

    ./gaiag                   main executable, see --help
    GNUmakefile               local makefile with handy tests, code coverage
    baseline/                 CSP and CODE baseline for handy diffing
    examples/                 example and test DZN input
    ./json2scm                JSON text to Scheme [] -> (), {} -> #,(hash)
    module/gaiag/om.scm       edit manually to switch to GOOPS or LIST
    module/gaiag/goops/       the GOOPS backend
    module/gaiag/list/        the plain list backend [default]
    module/gaiag/gaiag.scm    top level scheme file
    module/gaiag/resolve.scm  AST resolver
    module/gaiag/*.scm        language backends [c, c++, csp, dzn, ...]
    module/gaiag/*.scm        pseudo-language backends [ast, om, run, ...]
    module/gaiag/*.scm        library modules
    module/gaiag/json.scm     JSON library Aleix Conchillo Flaque
                 json/*.scm   (https://github.com/aconchillo/guile-json)
    module/gaiag/pretty-print.scm
                              Guile pretty printer; prints non-opaque hash-lists
    module/language/dezyne/   parser for DZN and plumbing to integrate DZN as
                              first class language in Guile [REPL/debugger]
    module/system/base/lalr*  LALR for Scheme by Dominique Boucher
                              (part of main Guile, but our upstream
                              modifications have not been released in Guile)
                              https://github.com/schemeway/lalr-scm
    patches/                  not-yet upstreamed patches
    runtime/                  dzn runtime for code languages
    ./scm2json                Scheme text to JSON () -> [], #,(hash) -> {}
    templates/                template files and snippets for output languages
    test-suite/tests/*.test   module tests
    test-suite/lib.scm        the Guile test framework, with LINE:COLUMN patch
